rminalPrompt`**: tests an implementation detail (env var literal). Acceptable as a regression test for #63 since the loud comment names the issue, but could equally be a single-line assertion in a broader `newGitCredentialCmd` test.\n\n## False positives (noted, moving on)\n\n- `Resolve` returning `nil, nil` repeated 3 times with `//nolint:nilnil` — pre-existing pattern, not new.\n- `isHTTPEndpoint` helper extraction (`auth.go:135-138`) — good dedupe, no concern.\n- `credentialInput` parameter signature `(ep, username, password)` — three params is fine; a struct would be over-engineering.\n\n## Summary\nMain asks: (1) drop `basicAuth` in favor of `transporthttp.BasicAuth`, (2) type the credential op as a constant set, (3) flatten retry block via extracted helper, (4) ruthlessly trim comments that narrate the change rather than encode a hidden invariant, (5) consolidate `fakeCredentialHelper`'s many counters into one `calls` slice and extract a `newTestConn` helper.\n\nKey files:\n- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/auth/auth.go`\n- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/gitproto/smarthttp.go`\n- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/gitproto/smarthttp_test.go`\n- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/auth/auth_test.go`\n- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/syncer/syncer.go`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aea877fdfc6628775 (use SendMessage with to: 'aea877fdfc6628775' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 48876\ntool_uses: 3\nduration_ms: 788464</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"41517c45-5d90-4ee6-89a8-024b5a2da086","timestamp":"2026-05-22T13:49:31.182Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You're reviewing a git-sync PR. Diff is at /tmp/issue-63-diff.patch. Repo root: /Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync.\n\nThe change defers `git credential fill` until a 401 response, instead of running it proactively. Implementation: new `CredentialHelper` interface on `gitproto.HTTPConn`, implemented b