{"parentUuid":"124101dc-daa2-4bb0-bd54-3268c5564e28","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"a796a250-277b-4b35-8738-65aa995aa7c1","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019rPfmdhCqAgFu3dndAHwWk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No internal-to-internal cycle. They're independent packages. The justification in the comment of `basicAuth` (\"without taking a dependency on go-git's transporthttp package\") is questionable — `auth.go` already takes that dependency, and it's the same module path. The real reason might be to keep `gitproto` zero-dependency on `go-git` types beyond what it already has (only `protocol/capability`), but that's a stylistic call.\n\nNow I have enough to report. Let me compile findings.\n\n## Findings: code reuse opportunities in PR #63\n\n### 1. `basicAuth` struct duplicates `transporthttp.BasicAuth` — **nit/discussion**\n\n`internal/gitproto/smarthttp.go:360-370` introduces:\n\n```go\ntype basicAuth struct { username, password string }\nfunc (b basicAuth) Authorizer(req *http.Request) error {\n    req.SetBasicAuth(b.username, b.password); return nil\n}\n```\n\nThis is byte-for-byte equivalent to `*transporthttp.BasicAuth` (`~/go/pkg/mod/github.com/go-git/go-git/v6@v6.0.0-alpha.3/plumbing/transport/http/auth.go:6-14`), which is what `auth.Resolve` already returns elsewhere (`internal/auth/auth.go:45,65`). The stated justification — \"without taking a dependency on go-git's transporthttp package\" — is weak because:\n- `internal/gitproto/smarthttp_test.go:15` already imports `transporthttp` in the same package.\n- `internal/auth/auth.go:12` already imports it; `c.Auth` can hold `*transporthttp.BasicAuth` returned by `Resolve`.\n- The `AuthMethod` doc comment at `smarthttp.go:67` literally cites `transporthttp.BasicAuth` and `transporthttp.TokenAuth` as the canonical satisfiers.\n\nA cleaner option is to return the credentials from `CredentialHelper.Lookup` (already happens) and have `auth.GitCredentialHelper.Lookup` (or a small constructor) hand back a `*transporthttp.BasicAuth` directly. Then `smarthttp.go` doesn't need its own auth type. Either change the `CredentialHelper` interface to return `AuthMethod` or have the gitproto retry path build `&transporthttp.BasicAuth{...}`. **Nit, not blocking** — but worth a comment.\n\n### 2. `GitCredentialHelper.Approve` and `Reject` are copy-paste twins — **strong**\n\n`internal/auth/auth.go:146-152` and `:156-162` differ only in the op string (\"approve\" / \"reject\"). Extract a private helper:\n\n```go\nfunc (GitCredentialHelper) signal(ctx context.Context, op string, ep *url.URL, username, password string) {\n    input := credentialInput(ep, username, password)\n    if input == \"\" { return }\n    _, _ = GitCredentialCommand(ctx, op, input)\n}\n```\n\nThen `Approve`/`Reject` become one-line wrappers. Cuts duplication and centralises the swallow-error contract.\n\n### 3. Username fallback duplicated — **nit**\n\n`internal/auth/auth.go:128-135` (in `Lookup`) re-implements the same \"empty username → URL user → `defaultGitUsername`\" fallback that `explicitAuth` does at `:60-64`. Not identical (Lookup also checks URL.User), but the `defaultGitUsername` last-resort is the same idea. Extract a tiny `resolveUsername(explicit string, ep *url.URL) string` helper. **Nit.**\n\n### 4. Test helpers `newAdvertisementResponse` / `newUnauthorizedResponse` could replace inline `http.Response` literals — **nit**\n\n`internal/gitproto/smarthttp_test.go:457-461, 464-471, 215-224, 574-581` build `*http.Response` by hand in pre-existing tests with the same shape now wrapped by `newAdvertisementResponse`/`newUnauthorizedResponse`. The new helpers are good additions; consider migrating the older inline literals while you're here. **Nit, drive-by cleanup.**\n\n### 5. Reject is called from two adjacent branches with identical args — **nit**\n\n`internal/gitproto/smarthttp.go:207` (transport error after retry) and `:219` (4xx after retry) both invoke `c.CredentialHelper.Reject(ctx, c.EndpointURL, user, pass)` with the same arguments. Not strictly duplication (different control flow), but the post-retry block could be restructured so reject lives once after the switch. Minor readability win.\n\n### 6. Test helpers `recordedCredCall`/`withRecordingHelper` are local to one file — **not a finding**\n\nThese are isolated to `internal/auth/auth_test.go` and don't have counterparts elsewhere — no reuse opportunity to flag.\n\n### Not findings (checked, no issue)\n\n- `isHTTPEndpoint` (`auth.go:140-142`) is genuinely new and is used twice (`Resolve`, `Lookup`); good extraction.\n- `newGitCredentialCmd` is appropriately factored out for the prompt-disable test.\n- `doInfoRefsRequest` extraction is correct and necessary for retry; doesn't duplicate `PostRPCStreamBody`'s setup beyond what an interface-level merger would complicate.\n- `parseCredentialOutput` already existed; no duplication.\n- `credentialInput` (renamed from `credentialFillInput`) is correctly generalised for fill/approve/reject — no duplication.\n\n### Summary\n\n- **Strong**: finding #2 (Approve/Reject duplication — collapse to one helper).\n- **Worth discussing**: finding #1 (`basicAuth` vs `transporthttp.BasicAuth` — the stated justification doesn't survive scrutiny; either delete the type or change the comment).\n- **Nits**: #3, #4, #5.\n\nRelevant files:\n- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/auth/auth.go`\n- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/gitproto/smarthttp.go`\n- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/internal/gitproto/smarthttp_test.go`\n- `/Users/soph/go/pkg/mod/github.com/go-git/go-git/v6@v6.0.0-alpha.3/plumbing/transport/http/auth.go` (reference for the equivalent type)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a056e11d3672f9c01 (use SendMessage with to: 'a056e11d3672f9c01' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 78370\ntool_uses: 27\nduration_ms: 6164973</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"0b2d9816-1f31-4c69-9cc6